@item --with-streams-kthreads=[OPTION]
@opindex streams-kthreads
When enabled (@option{OPTION} is @samp{normal} or @samp{rt}), the @dfn{STREAMS} scheduler runs as
a kernel thread.  When disabled (@option{OPTION} is @samp{no}), the @dfn{STREAMS} scheduler runs
as a software interrupt (bottom half).  Running the @dfn{STREAMS} scheduler at bottom half instead
of a kernel thread breaks the @file{strinet} and other drivers, that must be able to invoke kernel
functions that might sleep (but don't).
The option to set kernel threads to @samp{normal} or @samp{rt} priority was added during performance
testing.  A priority of @samp{normal} (nice -19) was found to provide significant performance
increase over @samp{rt} (real-time 99) due to significantly reduced context switching for a wide
range of STREAMS drivers and modules.
Therefore, this option defaults to @samp{normal}.
This option has not been tested in some time: do not set it to @samp{no}, and leave it set a
@samp{normal}.

